# SHAR Production — Final Premium Studio Pass

You are working on a premium AI/cinematic production studio website.

## Goal
Turn the current SHAR Production website into a world-class premium studio website while preserving the current business direction, current content, and current design concept.

The website must feel:
- premium
- minimal
- cinematic
- expensive
- restrained
- smooth
- technologically refined
- not template-like
- not Tilda-like
- not noisy

## Current known problems
- Journal exists only partially as a system: article pages exist, but top navigation still does not behave like a proper journal architecture.
- Contact page exists, but contact UX still feels weak and form visibility/clarity is not premium enough.
- Buttons still feel cheap and not premium enough.
- Visual surfaces and overall atmosphere still feel too dark/heavy or under-designed instead of expensive.
- Repo root is cluttered with planning markdown files and junk like .DS_Store.
- Site must be smoother, more polished, and more coherent.

## Priorities
1. Stable working architecture first.
2. Clean repo structure second.
3. Premium UX flows third.
4. Premium visual system fourth.
5. Performance and QA after every phase.

## Product standards

### Cases
- All case pages must work.
- All case pages must use one premium template.
- No broken routes.
- Case CTA must route into a strong contact flow.

### Journal
- There must be a dedicated journal landing page.
- Top navigation “Журнал” must open the journal landing page, not a weak pseudo-section behavior.
- Existing article pages must remain reachable.

### Contact
- Contact must feel premium, direct, and intentional.
- Real visible form fields must exist.
- Required fields:
  - name
  - phone or Telegram
  - optional company/project
  - short message
- Privacy policy must remain clearly linked.
- CTA flow must not feel generic or footer-like.

### Buttons
- Non-header buttons must look expensive and minimal.
- No cheap dark placeholder feel.
- No blunt heavy block fill.
- Use subtle premium hover fill, elegant border treatment, precise spacing, restrained motion.

### Visual direction
- luxury minimal tech
- premium studio
- dark but not muddy
- cinematic but not flashy
- expensive and clean
- more air, more precision, less template feel

### Repo hygiene
- Move planning/audit markdown files out of production root into /docs/ai/ or /docs/planning/.
- Remove junk files like .DS_Store.
- Keep production root clean.

## Workflow
Always do:
1. Audit
2. Safe plan
3. Implement only one bounded phase
4. QA that phase
5. Move on

Never do everything at once.
Never redesign blindly.
Never introduce flashy effects that hurt performance.